<p> </p>
<li><strong>The Law:</strong> To drive home the point that women lie beneath men within the societal order, Lauretta also comes back to Law and its relationship to women. The third story from the fourth day is the most telling of Lauretta's ideas. Maddalena, &quot;thought that by placating [the Duke's] desires she would be able to rescue her sister.&quot; The Duke embodies the law, and Maddalena sees nothing unusual or unsavory about sleeping with the representative of the law to achieve her own ends.
